org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.caching
Interface CacheProvider

All Known Implementing Classes:
NonCachingCacheProvider
public interface CacheProvider

Allows the developer to specify their own cache mechanism which will be used for all generic DAO method calls, write methods will automatically cause the cache to expire any related items
Note that your cache must be able to store null values (these are used to cache searches which come up with no results and are critical since these are often the most expensive searches and can cause full table scans)

Author:
Aaron Zeckoski (azeckoski@gmail.com)

Method Detail

createCache

void createCache(String cacheName)
Create a cache by the given name (or if the cache already exists then reset it), the cache will be used to cache one type of persistent objects, the cache only needs to exist in your implementation as it will be accessed using the given name

Parameters:
cacheName - a string which uniquely identifies this cache
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the cache name is invalid
IllegalStateException - if the cache cannot be created

put

void put(String cacheName,
         String key,
         Object value)
Puts an object in the specified cache

Parameters:
cacheName - a string which uniquely identifies this cache
key - the key for a persistent object (this will be the persistent id)
value - a persistent object (this can be a null to cache a miss)
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the cache name is invalid or cacheName or key is null

get

Object get(String cacheName,
           String key)
Gets an object from the cache if it can be found (maybe be a null), use the exists check to see if the object is in the cache before retrieving

Parameters:
cacheName - a string which uniquely identifies this cache
key - the key for a persistent object (this will be the persistent id)
Returns:
the cached persistent object (may be null)
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the cache name is invalid or any arguments are null
CacheKeyNotFoundException - if this key does not exist in the cache
